  "text": "Temperature was controlled with a bespoke incubator chamber, heated by a recirculating water bath (Grant Instruments Ltd, Cambridge, UK). A constant current circuit [CITATION_1] measured the resistance of NTC thermistors (Betatherm BT310-03M01 10kΩ, Shrewsbury, USA). This circuit was connected to a data acquisition card (DAQ, PCI-6221, National Instruments Corporation Ltd, UK). Sampling was performed at 10 Hz. The Steinhart-Hart equation coefficients provided by the supplier were used to calibrate the resistance-temperature relationship for the thermistor.",
